HEADWORD: Discodactylia
<hw>Dis`co*dac*tyl"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ disk + <?/ finger.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of amphibians having suctorial disks on the toes, as the
tree frogs.</def>⟦br⟧
